In a message dated 10/22/2001 8:43:58 AM Pacific Daylight Time, 
jbakerccymca(-at-)springmail.com writes:  << Can someone give me possible causes 
of valve chatter coming from what sounds like under the right side valve 
cover on a 40 HP engine? >>

Hi John,
Could be a screwed up/broken rocker arm, a broken push rod, a pulled out 
early studed head stud that holds down the rocker, or just a valve out of 
adjustment due to the mechanic not having tightened down the lock nut.
Eric&Barb
